The paper deals with algorithms for approximating the independence polynomial, which is a fundamental object in graph theory and combinatorics. The paper also discusses connections to statistical physics and the Lov\'{a}sz Local Lemma. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), statistical inference (cs.SI), and graph theory (cs.GT).
